South African rapper Cassper Nyovest released a new single on Friday morning The rapper and songwriter, whose real name is Refiloe Maele Phoolo, initially announced on social media that he was coming out with a single and album soon. The popular recording artist also revealed the title and album artwork in a tweet posted on Thursday. The 27-year-old recently released a music video for Waya Waya, featuring KO.  READ MORE: Cassper Nyovest and Distruction Boyz, nominated for BET Awards This morning, he posted the iTunes link on Twitter for his vernacular song Gets Getsa 2.0, with the caption: “Happy Gets Getsa season, gents!!!!”  Social media users could wait to give their opinion on Nyovest’s new single.       